## Optimization Techniques

### 1. Pre-process JSON Before Compression

**Before:**
```json
{
  "name": "Task 1",
  "emptyField": "",
  "nullField": null,
  "description": "Description"
}
```

**After:**
```json
{
  "name":"Task 1",
  "description":"Description"
}
```

**Savings:** Remove empty values, minimize whitespace → +10-15% compression

### 2. Compress Exports (.brain files)

```typescript
// brainBackup.ts
const compressed = gzip(JSON.stringify(data));
// Result: ~70% size reduction
```

### 3. Image Optimization (Future - when images in notes shipped)

```typescript
// Resize large images before IndexedDB storage
const maxWidth = 1920;
const maxHeight = 1080;
const quality = 0.85; // 85% JPEG quality

// Result: ~60-80% size reduction for photos
```

### 4. Code Splitting by Route

```typescript
// App.tsx
const Dashboard = React.lazy(() => import('./pages/Dashboard'));
const Notes = React.lazy(() => import('./pages/Notes'));
const Kanban = React.lazy(() => import('./widgets/Kanban'));
const Calendar = React.lazy(() => import('./widgets/Calendar'));
const Settings = React.lazy(() => import('./pages/Settings'));
```

**Result:** Each page loads only when navigated to

