## Anti-Patterns (What NOT to Do)

### ❌ Anti-Pattern 1: Import Entire Libraries

```typescript
// Adds 100KB to bundle
import _ from 'lodash';

// ✅ Better: Use lodash-es with named imports (tree-shakeable)
import { debounce } from 'lodash-es';
```

### ❌ Anti-Pattern 2: Inline Heavy Dependencies

```typescript
// Adds Chart.js (200KB) to every page
import Chart from 'chart.js';

function Dashboard() {
  return <Chart data={data} />; // Loads even if chart never rendered
}

// ✅ Better: Lazy load when actually needed
const Chart = React.lazy(() => import('./Chart'));
```

### ❌ Anti-Pattern 3: Duplicate Dependencies

```typescript
// Using both moment.js AND date-fns (170KB combined!)
import moment from 'moment';
import { format } from 'date-fns';

// ✅ Better: Pick one and stick with it
import { format } from 'date-fns'; // We chose date-fns (smaller)
```

### ❌ Anti-Pattern 4: No Code Splitting

```typescript
// All features load on initial page (1MB+)
import Dashboard from './Dashboard';
import Kanban from './Kanban';
import Calendar from './Calendar';
import Notes from './Notes';

// ✅ Better: Use React.lazy() for route-based splitting
```

