## Real-World Examples

### Example 1: Lexical Editor (Sprint 4)

**Before:**
- Bundled with main chunk
- Initial load: 362KB
- Time to interactive: 2-3s

**After:**
- Created lexical-vendor chunk (79KB)
- Lazy loaded on Notes page access
- Initial load: 126KB
- Time to interactive: < 1s
- **Result:** 65% reduction

### Example 2: AI Terminal (Sprint 5)

**Before approach (hypothetical):**
- Bundle all 8 AI SDKs with main chunk
- Initial load: 500KB+

**Actual approach:**
- Created ai-vendor chunk (45KB)
- Lazy loaded on AI Terminal open
- Initial load: 126KB (unchanged)
- **Result:** Zero impact on initial load

### Example 3: Dashboard Widgets (Sprint 6)

**Smart approach:**
- Each widget is lazy loaded independently (1-5KB each)
- Widget library modal loads widget metadata only (< 1KB)
- Actual widget code loads when added to dashboard
- **Result:** 40+ widgets, zero initial load impact

